The paper discusses the execution of smart contracts in blockchain platforms, which involves distributed computing, consensus protocols, and transaction processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the validation of smart contracts, which involves security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The use of conflict graphs and transaction ordering protocols suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique for concurrent execution of smart contracts, which involves software engineering and system design, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible category as well.
